nner that appears\nto be proportional to the bulk connectivity length. This suggests that a\npercolation transition in the bulk also drives a similar divergence observed in\nsurfactant templated polyacrylamide gels at high surfactant concentrations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Jan 2002 23:19:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 May 2002 13:22:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
